-- Colombian Stock Movers: Canacol Energy Ltd., Valorem SA Advance
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-02-14T17:40:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/colombian-stock-movers-canacol-energy-ltd-valorem-sa-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:23 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.3 percent to 14,201.82 while the
Colcap Index was little changed at 1,669.19.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  Colombia , gained 0.9 percent to
1,635 pesos.  The company said its Carrao Energy Sucursal Colombia unit
has increased its stakes in the Santa Isabel and LLA 23
contracts. The company increased its stake in Santa Isabel by 10
percent to 100 percent and in LLA by 9 percent to 80 percent,
according to a statement.  Valorem SA (VALOREM)  (VALOREM CB), the Colombian holding company with
interests in broadcasting and manufacturing, rose 7.1 percent to
393 pesos. The shares gained 45 percent in the past week.  Virgin Mobile  Latin America  and Valorem’s Cine Colombia SA
unit created a partnership to attract clients for Virgin
Mobile’s plan to offer cellular phone services in Colombia in
the second half of 2012, according to a Feb. 2 e-mailed
statement from Virgin Mobile.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
